b'Child care'
b'College is for everyone, even the young ones. The UIC Children\xe2\x80\x99s Center is fully accredited, full-time early childhood education for children of faculty, staff and students, ages 2 years, 9 months to 6 years.\nUIC Children\xe2\x80\x99s Center\n312-413-5326'
b' UIC Children\xe2\x80\x99s Center'
b'\xc2\xa0'
b'Commuter Student Resource Center '
b'UIC\xe2\x80\x99s Commuter Student Resource Center, the hub for Commuter and Off-Campus Programs, provides a home away from home for commuter students. Inside the Wellness Center, 240-248 Student Center East \xe2\x80\x94 behind the Inner Circle food court \xe2\x80\x94 it has quiet study space, social lounge, public computers and printers, kitchen and lockers. Staff can provide information on transportation, off-campus housing and other resources.'
b'Commuter Student Resource Center'
b'Mon.\xe2\x80\x93Thurs. 7:30 a.m. to 6 p.m.\nFri. 7:30 a.m. to 5 p.m.\n312-413-7440'
